WEBVTT

00:00:02.440 --> 00:00:04.670
- <i>Previously on</i> The O. C:
- You gotta have a plan.

00:00:04.840 --> 00:00:05.955
Yeah. Right.

00:00:06.120 --> 00:00:09.510
- Who are you?
- I stole a car. Crashed it.

00:00:09.680 --> 00:00:12.069
Then my mom threw me out.
So Mr. Cohen took me in.

00:00:12.240 --> 00:00:14.595
- You brought him home?
- What do you guys do around here?

00:00:14.760 --> 00:00:17.593
- What do you think of Newport?
- I can get in less trouble where I'm from.

00:00:17.760 --> 00:00:20.115
- You have no idea.
- Shouldn't her boyfriend do this?

00:00:20.280 --> 00:00:22.475
Sure they're not doing anything
we didn't do.

00:00:22.640 --> 00:00:25.234
- My dad's not here.
- It's just a thing with a client.

00:00:25.400 --> 00:00:26.799
- Put him down.
- Hey, Ryan.

00:00:27.680 --> 00:00:30.558
- Welcome to the O.C., bitch.
- I don't want this kid in my house.

00:00:52.000 --> 00:00:55.595
Guys, come on. Out of the pool.
Dinner's almost ready.

00:00:59.160 --> 00:01:01.116
Dad, I know.

00:01:02.240 --> 00:01:06.677
I understand how important the model
home is to the new development.

00:01:07.400 --> 00:01:10.756
We'll sell the lots by Christmas,
I promise.

00:01:11.200 --> 00:01:12.838
Okay. Bye.

00:01:15.840 --> 00:01:17.592
I wish there was more we could do.

00:01:17.760 --> 00:01:20.638
Honey, you're his lawyer,
not his guardian.

00:01:20.800 --> 00:01:24.475
I know. In the morning
I'll take him to Child Services.

00:01:26.760 --> 00:01:29.911
What kind of mother
just abandons her child?

00:01:32.680 --> 00:01:35.513
- What happens if they don't find her?
- He'll go into the system.

00:01:35.680 --> 00:01:38.558
Foster care till he's 18.
I mean, they'll try and place him...

00:01:38.720 --> 00:01:41.996
...but at his age it'll be impossible.

00:01:50.280 --> 00:01:52.430
You know what I was thinking?

00:01:54.120 --> 00:01:57.396
This being your last night and all,
we should do something special.

00:01:57.920 --> 00:01:59.512
I don't know what.

00:01:59.680 --> 00:02:04.071
Possibly get a couple of tattoos or some
hookers and lose our virginity, right?

00:02:04.920 --> 00:02:09.391
Okay, dude, there's a shark movie
at the IMAX if that's what you're into.

00:02:12.160 --> 00:02:13.912
I think I just want to take it easy.

00:02:19.760 --> 00:02:21.955
How was your swim?

00:02:22.120 --> 00:02:23.792
It was great.

00:02:23.960 --> 00:02:25.632
What's that?

00:02:26.360 --> 00:02:28.590
It's a model home.

00:02:30.720 --> 00:02:34.156
I build them.
Well, the real ones, not that one.

00:02:34.320 --> 00:02:35.958
Can you build me one?

00:02:37.920 --> 00:02:40.195
Sorry. Bad joke.

00:02:45.280 --> 00:02:46.713
Thanks.

00:02:49.760 --> 00:02:50.988
So...

00:02:51.160 --> 00:02:53.116
...the last supper, huh?

00:02:54.520 --> 00:02:56.192
Sorry. Bad joke.

00:02:56.360 --> 00:02:58.237
It's just a laugh riot around here.

00:02:58.400 --> 00:03:00.755
- This all looks really good.
- Too bad you're leaving.

00:03:00.920 --> 00:03:04.310
- We never eat like this.
- That's not true. I cook all the time.

00:03:04.480 --> 00:03:05.833
Dad.

00:03:06.000 --> 00:03:08.514
I'm sorry, honey.

00:03:10.480 --> 00:03:11.469
Let's just eat.

00:03:11.760 --> 00:03:13.876
We're not saying
we want you to cook more.

00:03:14.040 --> 00:03:16.793
- Remember the meat loaf incident of '98?
- That was brisket.

00:03:16.960 --> 00:03:19.952
Yeah, that's my point exactly.

00:03:24.840 --> 00:03:26.796
As your attorney, I'll cosign these forms.

00:03:26.960 --> 00:03:31.272
They basically say that you don't have
a legal parent or a guardian available.

00:03:31.440 --> 00:03:35.433
So I'm now property of the
government, nickname 0382965.

00:03:35.600 --> 00:03:38.433
Hey, it's better than "Death Breath Seth."

00:03:38.600 --> 00:03:40.318
Or so I would imagine.

00:03:41.440 --> 00:03:43.908
So we'll meet with your social worker
in the morning...

00:03:44.080 --> 00:03:48.631
...and she'll be the one
to take you to the group home.

00:03:49.080 --> 00:03:53.278
My contact at Child Services got you in
with only two other kids, which is good.

00:03:53.440 --> 00:03:56.989
- It can get crowded.
- Thanks. I appreciate it.

00:03:57.800 --> 00:03:59.358
And, you know...

00:03:59.520 --> 00:04:01.988
...they do find foster homes
for kids your age.

00:04:02.160 --> 00:04:04.833
Yeah, because everybody wants
a brand-new teenager.

00:04:06.400 --> 00:04:08.960
I'm sorry if I'm the only one
that'll state the obvious...

00:04:09.120 --> 00:04:11.554
...but we have all this extra room.
We have a pool house.

00:04:11.720 --> 00:04:15.190
Yet you guys are gonna ship him off
to a group home? Am I the only one...

00:04:15.360 --> 00:04:18.875
...who gets how much that sucks?
- It's okay. Really.

00:04:24.440 --> 00:04:26.556
Good luck with it. It looks perfect.

00:04:28.000 --> 00:04:30.833
- Good night.
- Good night.

00:05:48.560 --> 00:05:51.154
Hey, how about a little...

00:05:51.320 --> 00:05:53.276
...PlayStation perhaps?

00:05:53.440 --> 00:05:56.352
- Are you running away?
- Go back in the house, Seth.

00:05:56.520 --> 00:05:58.636
Hey, you can't just run away.

00:05:58.800 --> 00:06:02.236
What are you thinking?
What about Child Services or my dad?

00:06:05.000 --> 00:06:07.116
Okay, then wait.
I want to come with you.

00:06:07.960 --> 00:06:11.396
Know what I've always wanted to do,
besides sail to Tahiti? That Kerouac thing.

00:06:11.560 --> 00:06:15.155
Hit the road, stop at diner to diner,
the pancake tour of North America.

00:06:16.520 --> 00:06:17.794
- No.
- Fair enough.

00:06:17.960 --> 00:06:20.520
- Where you going?
- I don't know.

00:06:20.800 --> 00:06:22.631
New town, get a job, save some money.

00:06:22.800 --> 00:06:24.756
Great plan.
You've given it a lot of thought.

00:06:24.920 --> 00:06:26.751
Got a better idea?

00:06:30.320 --> 00:06:32.311
Actually, I do.

00:06:42.440 --> 00:06:44.078
Seth?

00:06:50.640 --> 00:06:52.790
Can I talk to you?

00:06:54.080 --> 00:06:55.832
Dad?

00:06:57.560 --> 00:07:00.836
- What, is it morning?
- You're asleep?

00:07:01.760 --> 00:07:04.115
Yeah, I was. What's going on?

00:07:04.520 --> 00:07:06.192
Well...

00:07:06.360 --> 00:07:07.873
...I wanted to talk about Ryan.

00:07:08.040 --> 00:07:10.270
Yeah, I know. It's cool.
We don't need to discuss it.

00:07:10.440 --> 00:07:14.592
I think we do. I know you're upset,
your mother and I are upset.

00:07:14.760 --> 00:07:17.115
But our responsibility is to our family.

00:07:17.280 --> 00:07:20.113
It's okay. I get it.
This is a person's life we're talking about.

00:07:20.280 --> 00:07:22.635
We need to leave it
in the hands of the authorities.

00:07:22.800 --> 00:07:25.473
- There's no need for sarcasm.
- I'm not being sarcastic.

00:07:26.080 --> 00:07:28.071
Well, it's hard to tell sometimes.

00:07:28.240 --> 00:07:30.231
Dad?

00:07:30.400 --> 00:07:32.868
It's okay. Really.

00:07:33.480 --> 00:07:37.792
- When you want to talk about it...
- I know. You're the one to talk to. Got it.

00:07:37.960 --> 00:07:39.279
Good night.

00:07:41.160 --> 00:07:43.549
- Good night.
- Night.

00:07:53.360 --> 00:07:54.998
Come on, Seth.

00:08:00.560 --> 00:08:03.916
Okay, got it. I'll be there in,
like, 20 minutes.

00:08:10.160 --> 00:08:12.958
- Hey.
- Hey.

00:08:13.720 --> 00:08:15.915
I didn't think I'd see you again.

00:08:17.560 --> 00:08:20.154
Look, I wanted to say thanks
for the other night.

00:08:21.000 --> 00:08:22.911
You always drink like that?

00:08:25.880 --> 00:08:30.192
- I thought you left.
- I did. I am.

00:08:30.360 --> 00:08:33.796
Ryan. Ryan, I'm all set. Ready?

00:08:34.880 --> 00:08:36.472
Hi there, Marissa.

00:08:36.640 --> 00:08:39.359
- What are you doing?
- Nothing. We're just hanging out.

00:08:39.520 --> 00:08:42.592
Look, it's somebody's birthday.
My invitation got lost in the mail.

00:08:42.760 --> 00:08:44.796
It's my friend Summer's birthday.

00:08:44.960 --> 00:08:47.076
Summer's birthday is not till Wednesday.

00:08:48.080 --> 00:08:50.116
That's what I heard.
I don't know. I guessed.

00:08:50.280 --> 00:08:52.475
You guys are up to something.

00:08:52.880 --> 00:08:56.395
- Dude, what did you tell her?
- I didn't tell her anything.

00:08:57.160 --> 00:08:59.549
Maybe the black turtleneck in August
tipped her off.

00:08:59.720 --> 00:09:03.633
Okay, I was going for stealth.
Also, it's slimming.

00:09:03.800 --> 00:09:06.234
We should really go.
Have fun at your party.

00:09:06.400 --> 00:09:09.312
You should probably be off.
The Newport social scene awaits.

00:09:11.280 --> 00:09:13.111
Oh, yeah?

00:09:15.200 --> 00:09:18.795
Why won't you tell me where we're
going? This is pretty far away.

00:09:18.960 --> 00:09:23.272
Oh, wow, complaining. That's interesting,
considering nobody invited you.

00:09:23.440 --> 00:09:26.716
Before I came along
you were on a skateboard.

00:09:32.800 --> 00:09:34.791
- You like them?
- Yeah, I guess.

00:09:34.960 --> 00:09:38.191
- Well, what do you like?
- Everything.

00:09:38.680 --> 00:09:40.636
I don't know,
I don't really listen to music.

00:09:41.000 --> 00:09:43.560
- Dude, that's kind of weird.
- Why? What do you like?

00:09:44.120 --> 00:09:46.588
Right now, punk.

00:09:46.760 --> 00:09:48.830
Avril Lavigne doesn't count as punk.

00:09:49.000 --> 00:09:53.915
What about the Cramps?
Stiff Little Fingers. The Clash. Sex Pistols.

00:09:54.320 --> 00:09:57.756
I listen to the same music
as Marissa Cooper?

00:09:57.920 --> 00:10:00.832
- I think I have to kill myself.
- You listen to punk, huh?

00:10:01.000 --> 00:10:02.672
I'm angry.

00:10:04.280 --> 00:10:05.872
That's it right there.

00:10:11.080 --> 00:10:14.356
- Looks scary.
- Then you can stay in the car.

00:10:17.800 --> 00:10:20.030
Do you recognize this place, Ryan?

00:10:20.200 --> 00:10:21.918
- This isn't...
- Where are we?

00:10:22.080 --> 00:10:24.594
Well, it's one of my mom's
housing developments.

00:10:24.760 --> 00:10:27.593
Her and my grandpa own a bunch
of them. This is supposed to be...

00:10:27.760 --> 00:10:30.991
...the model home,
but it never got finished.

00:10:31.400 --> 00:10:33.789
Why? Did someone die here
and now it's haunted?

00:10:33.960 --> 00:10:35.757
Yes. That's exactly what happened.

00:10:35.920 --> 00:10:38.718
- What did happen?
- I don't know.

00:10:38.880 --> 00:10:41.235
<i>How do contractors just disappear?</i>

00:10:41.400 --> 00:10:44.870
If we don't have a model home,
we don't have a new development.

00:10:45.440 --> 00:10:49.513
It's been a month.
I'm not waiting for you guys anymore.

00:10:51.480 --> 00:10:54.677
- You know where to reach me.
- No luck with the contractors?

00:10:54.840 --> 00:10:56.239
Vanished.

00:10:56.680 --> 00:10:59.638
My father's never gonna
let me hear the end of this.

00:11:00.680 --> 00:11:02.750
Did you...? Did you talk to Seth?

00:11:04.800 --> 00:11:06.836
I think so. Don't blame yourself.

00:11:07.000 --> 00:11:11.835
I'm not blaming myself. But how can I
allow a strange boy to live in this house?

00:11:12.000 --> 00:11:14.275
Seth needs to know
it's what any mother would do.

00:11:15.720 --> 00:11:17.711
I was talking about the contractors.

00:11:23.200 --> 00:11:25.350
So you want him to stay here?

00:11:25.520 --> 00:11:28.592
Well, I mean, I know the place
needs some sprucing up, but...

00:11:28.760 --> 00:11:31.593
God, did I just say "sprucing"?

00:11:31.760 --> 00:11:33.671
So, Ryan, what do you think?

00:11:33.840 --> 00:11:35.751
I haven't really had time to think.

00:11:35.920 --> 00:11:38.309
But how much better is this place
than some group home?

00:11:38.480 --> 00:11:40.675
And wait till you see the best part.

00:11:49.320 --> 00:11:52.198
- It's an empty pool.
- To some people.

00:11:54.800 --> 00:11:59.316
So your mom... I mean,
she has to come back, right?

00:11:59.480 --> 00:12:03.758
I don't know.
My mom's kind of a train wreck.

00:12:04.360 --> 00:12:06.669
So's mine.

00:12:10.520 --> 00:12:13.193
What about your dad?
Can you call him?

00:12:13.360 --> 00:12:16.557
Dad's in jail. Armed robbery.

00:12:16.840 --> 00:12:18.034
Impressive, huh?

00:12:23.720 --> 00:12:28.840
My dad, he's, like, a financial planner.
And I think he's in trouble.

00:12:29.720 --> 00:12:31.551
I don't have any stock tips.

00:12:33.720 --> 00:12:35.631
He stopped going to the office.

00:12:35.800 --> 00:12:39.759
And these guys keep showing up
at the door, like cops.

00:12:39.920 --> 00:12:42.150
But he won't answer.

00:12:44.680 --> 00:12:47.717
- Look, I haven't told anybody that.
- I can keep a secret.

00:12:54.600 --> 00:12:57.353
- Hey.
- <i>Where you at, girl?</i>

00:12:57.520 --> 00:13:00.193
It's time for you to get your buzz on.

00:13:00.400 --> 00:13:02.595
Nordlund is so faded
he can't even feel his feet.

00:13:02.760 --> 00:13:04.955
There goes the left leg!

00:13:06.280 --> 00:13:09.352
I miss you, babe. You know
it's not a party without you.

00:13:09.520 --> 00:13:11.511
- Oh, you're sweet.
- <i>What's the deal?</i>

00:13:11.680 --> 00:13:13.432
<i>You were supposed to be here</i>
<i>an hour ago.</i>

00:13:13.600 --> 00:13:15.511
Okay, I'll be there soon.

00:13:16.080 --> 00:13:17.513
Say hi to everyone.

00:13:18.280 --> 00:13:20.350
All right. Love you.

00:13:21.000 --> 00:13:22.592
Love you too.

00:13:23.400 --> 00:13:24.594
Bye.

00:13:36.280 --> 00:13:38.430
So how long you been with him?

00:13:38.600 --> 00:13:40.158
Luke?

00:13:40.680 --> 00:13:42.272
- I don't know, really.
- I know.

00:13:42.920 --> 00:13:45.150
Fifth grade, when you two
got your mack on...

00:13:45.320 --> 00:13:48.517
...during our class trip to the
Museum of Tolerance, back of the bus.

00:13:48.680 --> 00:13:49.669
Classy lady.

00:13:50.000 --> 00:13:52.355
You know what?
What's your problem, Cohen?

00:13:52.600 --> 00:13:54.830
- I mean, what did I ever do to you?
- Nothing.

00:13:55.000 --> 00:13:58.788
I've lived next door to you forever, and
you've never done or said anything to me.

00:13:59.480 --> 00:14:01.630
Oh, my God. You're the one
who never talks to me.

00:14:01.800 --> 00:14:03.836
You think you're so much better
than everyone.

00:14:04.000 --> 00:14:05.672
I do?

00:14:07.240 --> 00:14:10.357
Well, if you're talking about Luke,
then, yes...

00:14:10.520 --> 00:14:12.954
...because that guy shaves his chest!

00:14:14.360 --> 00:14:15.679
He plays water polo.

00:14:15.840 --> 00:14:18.434
We know. Half the team
tried to kill us the other night.

00:14:19.480 --> 00:14:21.516
I'm not too popular around here.

00:14:21.680 --> 00:14:23.113
And your boyfriend...

00:14:23.280 --> 00:14:24.349
...a little bit angry.

00:14:24.520 --> 00:14:28.433
- You didn't try to hit him back?
- Actually, I hit him first.

00:14:28.600 --> 00:14:31.558
Well, hard to believe
you're not more popular.

00:14:33.760 --> 00:14:36.228
I thought this could be your room.

00:14:39.280 --> 00:14:41.748
I still don't know if it's a good idea
for me to stick around.

00:14:41.920 --> 00:14:43.876
You should stay.

00:14:45.880 --> 00:14:50.271
- Okay. For a little while.
- So when she says it, you listen?

00:14:53.000 --> 00:14:55.798
- Hey, Summer.
- Hey, is that Summer?

00:14:57.000 --> 00:14:59.309
- Tell her I said happy birthday.
- Okay.

00:14:59.480 --> 00:15:01.789
Coop, where are you?
We're coming to get you.

00:15:01.960 --> 00:15:04.030
Oh, no, don't. I'm coming.

00:15:04.200 --> 00:15:08.034
- Tell her I said happy birthday.
- Seth Cohen says happy birthday.

00:15:08.200 --> 00:15:10.953
- Who?
- She says thanks.

00:15:13.560 --> 00:15:16.199
Look, I gotta go. Okay. Bye.

00:15:17.400 --> 00:15:19.436
I gotta go meet my friends.

00:15:20.200 --> 00:15:21.633
My other friends.

00:15:21.800 --> 00:15:23.756
I should get back too
and protect my cover.

00:15:23.920 --> 00:15:27.913
But wait. Listen. We have to promise
not to tell anyone about this place, okay?

00:15:28.080 --> 00:15:31.231
Now, Ryan's not going to, obviously,
and I could get grounded.

00:15:31.400 --> 00:15:34.073
So that leaves Marissa.

00:15:34.240 --> 00:15:36.356
I can keep a secret.

00:15:37.560 --> 00:15:39.596
Okay. See you tomorrow.

00:15:40.200 --> 00:15:42.191
Me too. We'll fix this place up.

00:15:47.280 --> 00:15:49.396
- Cool.
- I'm telling you, Ryan...

00:15:49.600 --> 00:15:51.511
...this plan is foolproof.

00:16:07.800 --> 00:16:09.358
Ryan?

00:16:10.600 --> 00:16:12.830
Hey, Ryan? You ready?

00:16:28.920 --> 00:16:32.674
Okay, the key here is not to panic.
Do you have your supplies?

00:16:32.840 --> 00:16:36.196
Yeah, but there are cops at your house.
Do you think it's safe?

00:16:36.360 --> 00:16:39.591
I'll handle Johnny Law, unless...
Are you losing your nerve?

00:16:39.760 --> 00:16:40.954
Meet me in the driveway.

00:16:44.760 --> 00:16:48.389
He couldn't have gotten far.
We'll search the neighborhood.

00:16:48.560 --> 00:16:52.030
Seth, I was just gonna get you.
We gotta talk about Ryan.

00:16:55.520 --> 00:16:58.239
Marissa, look who's here.

00:17:00.600 --> 00:17:04.070
- Luke, hi.
- Hey.

00:17:04.320 --> 00:17:06.993
Just grabbing a little grub
before we take the boat out.

00:17:07.160 --> 00:17:08.593
Boat?

00:17:08.760 --> 00:17:10.512
I thought we'd take my dad's Donzi.

00:17:10.680 --> 00:17:13.433
Do a little waterskiing,
have a little lunch.

00:17:20.440 --> 00:17:22.556
So you have no idea
where Ryan might have gone?

00:17:22.720 --> 00:17:24.153
I don't know.

00:17:24.320 --> 00:17:26.470
He did say something about
going down to Mexico...

00:17:26.640 --> 00:17:29.200
...and gambling on cockfights.
I mean, I don't know what...

00:17:29.360 --> 00:17:31.510
Quit joking. Answer his question.

00:17:31.680 --> 00:17:36.754
Yes, I did. I really don't know. I do not
know the guy. I never got the chance.

00:17:40.000 --> 00:17:41.149
Hey, there's eggs.

00:17:41.920 --> 00:17:44.673
Oh, I'm taking Kaitlin to the stables,
so I need that check.

00:17:45.040 --> 00:17:46.678
Does Kaitlin really need a pony?

00:17:46.840 --> 00:17:49.195
In a couple months,
she's not even gonna like horses.

00:17:49.360 --> 00:17:52.193
What? I love China.
She's the prettiest pony.

00:17:52.360 --> 00:17:53.509
We're not giving up China.

00:17:53.680 --> 00:17:56.513
Wait in the car, sweetie.
Mommy will be right with you.

00:18:01.760 --> 00:18:05.150
Jimmy, all this work
is making you so tense.

00:18:05.320 --> 00:18:06.992
Look, I gotta...

00:18:07.160 --> 00:18:08.957
I've gotta talk to you
about work.

00:18:09.120 --> 00:18:11.680
You know I don't like to talk
about work.

00:18:11.840 --> 00:18:14.912
Yeah, well, I've made...

00:18:15.080 --> 00:18:17.071
...a few mistakes...

00:18:17.240 --> 00:18:18.878
...and I don't know really...

00:18:19.040 --> 00:18:22.032
Jimmy, you don't have cancer.
No one is dying.

00:18:22.200 --> 00:18:26.239
Whatever it is, whatever you've done,
I'm sure you'll fix it.

00:18:26.400 --> 00:18:29.437
Can you write that check?
I don't want Kaitlin to be late. Okay?

00:18:30.960 --> 00:18:34.350
It's just, Suki is amazing. It doesn't
hurt at all when she's waxing you.

00:18:34.520 --> 00:18:36.112
It's really hard to get an appointment.

00:18:36.280 --> 00:18:38.635
Why don't you get a manicure?
You could come with me.

00:18:38.800 --> 00:18:40.995
I mean, they're not just for girls.

00:18:41.160 --> 00:18:43.390
You go. We'll catch up later.

00:18:43.560 --> 00:18:45.278
Holly's having a...

00:18:46.120 --> 00:18:48.111
- Holly's having a thing.
- Perfect.

00:18:56.040 --> 00:19:00.750
- So did you tell him anything?
- No. But if anyone asks, you're Suki.

00:19:02.480 --> 00:19:04.118
So you didn't tell them anything?

00:19:05.280 --> 00:19:08.989
Actually, I told them you went
to Mexico for cockfights.

00:19:09.160 --> 00:19:10.991
You know what,
even if they don't believe me...

00:19:11.160 --> 00:19:12.991
...they'll never look for you here.

00:19:14.880 --> 00:19:17.474
- Did you seriously bring a loofa?
- What's a loofa?

00:19:17.640 --> 00:19:19.596
You said bring whatever
was around the house.

00:19:19.760 --> 00:19:23.116
But I meant, like, survival supplies,
like rope or muskets...

00:19:23.280 --> 00:19:27.512
...and not Kiehl's cucumber moisturizer.

00:19:32.680 --> 00:19:35.672
- That's a pretty good call.
- That's nice.

00:19:44.280 --> 00:19:45.759
Hey.

00:19:47.120 --> 00:19:48.951
Here's a little bit of everything.

00:19:49.560 --> 00:19:51.232
Let your education begin.

00:19:54.120 --> 00:19:56.475
This place is perfect.
Seriously, it's totally safe.

00:19:56.640 --> 00:19:59.108
Ryan, how perfect is this place, right?

00:19:59.280 --> 00:20:02.511
- What else could you need?
- Anyone bring any food?

00:20:03.520 --> 00:20:06.114
Food. Guess we're going on a mission.

00:20:24.640 --> 00:20:26.232
Faster! Come on!

00:20:49.560 --> 00:20:53.758
Call me if someone meeting that
description comes in. Thank you.

00:20:53.920 --> 00:20:56.195
- Nothing at the hospitals.
- I'm sure he'll turn up.

00:20:56.360 --> 00:20:58.078
I think Seth knows where he is.

00:20:58.240 --> 00:21:02.438
Are you accusing him of lying?
That'll be good for your relationship.

00:21:02.600 --> 00:21:06.309
- Let the police handle this.
- I wish you hadn't called the police.

00:21:06.480 --> 00:21:08.789
They don't have the resources
or the manpower.

00:21:08.960 --> 00:21:10.473
Ryan will slip through the cracks.

00:21:10.640 --> 00:21:12.631
Sandy, how many of these cases
have you seen...

00:21:12.800 --> 00:21:15.360
...have passed across your desk?

00:21:20.000 --> 00:21:21.274
What is it about this kid?

00:21:22.120 --> 00:21:25.669
I thought I could help him,
make a difference.

00:21:25.840 --> 00:21:27.796
I was this kid.

00:21:28.640 --> 00:21:30.676
If someone hadn't helped me...

00:21:32.520 --> 00:21:34.397
...I wouldn't be here.

00:21:40.400 --> 00:21:41.958
Hello?

00:21:47.280 --> 00:21:51.034
- How are you?
- I'm good. I hate to ask, but...

00:21:51.200 --> 00:21:53.156
...I need your help with something.

00:21:53.320 --> 00:21:54.753
Of course.

00:21:56.000 --> 00:21:59.549
China has alopecia.
We need to call the vet.

00:22:03.440 --> 00:22:06.876
- Are you free for lunch?
- Yeah.

00:22:07.040 --> 00:22:11.079
I have some stuff I need to do for work,
but lunch sounds great.

00:22:11.920 --> 00:22:14.798
So, you guys,
I've been thinking about a plan.

00:22:15.480 --> 00:22:18.313
You know, right now,
this could very well be...

00:22:18.480 --> 00:22:21.119
...the first stop on our pancake tour
of North America.

00:22:21.280 --> 00:22:23.953
Like in <i>On the Road?</i>
That's my favorite book.

00:22:25.360 --> 00:22:27.078
Mine too.

00:22:28.040 --> 00:22:29.473
So here's the deal.

00:22:29.640 --> 00:22:33.553
My mom had this boyfriend, he hired me
to work construction last summer.

00:22:33.720 --> 00:22:38.157
But then they broke up.
He moved away to Austin.

00:22:38.680 --> 00:22:40.079
In Texas.

00:22:40.240 --> 00:22:43.710
- He said if I was ever there, look him up.
- Well, I mean...

00:22:43.880 --> 00:22:47.668
That's kind of far. We were thinking, like,
Long Beach, so we could still hang out.

00:22:47.840 --> 00:22:50.673
I'll need to get a couple days of work
so I can get travel money.

00:22:50.840 --> 00:22:52.637
Well, I mean, we can get you money.

00:22:57.760 --> 00:23:00.354
Well, I mean, you know,
I guess in a way you're lucky.

00:23:00.520 --> 00:23:04.354
You get to move to a new place,
start over, be whoever you want to be.

00:23:04.520 --> 00:23:06.954
That's really not so bad.

00:23:12.800 --> 00:23:14.074
Hey.

00:23:15.360 --> 00:23:17.715
- What's it take to get a menu?
- I'll handle it.

00:23:17.880 --> 00:23:19.916
- No, I'll handle it.
- And ruin your popularity?

00:23:20.080 --> 00:23:23.470
You know what, why don't you guys
just sneak out the back.

00:23:25.920 --> 00:23:27.717
What's going on with you two?

00:23:28.160 --> 00:23:30.515
Hey, how's it going?

00:23:31.840 --> 00:23:35.310
Oh, it was great. It was really good.

00:23:37.280 --> 00:23:39.840
Hey! Front door.

00:23:44.240 --> 00:23:47.357
- I was thinking we could go to Holly's.
- Thanks.

00:23:47.520 --> 00:23:49.397
- Sounds good.
- Awesome.

00:23:49.560 --> 00:23:51.835
So, what did you guys do today?

00:23:55.800 --> 00:23:58.837
Hi. How you doing? You like
the food here too? It's pretty awesome.

00:23:59.000 --> 00:24:00.797
Shut up, queer.

00:24:01.560 --> 00:24:03.357
Well, at least I don't shave my chest.

00:24:03.520 --> 00:24:05.431
- What did you say?
- Luke, come on.

00:24:05.600 --> 00:24:08.319
I said, you look nice in a sweater vest.
It was a compliment.

00:24:08.480 --> 00:24:11.517
- Do you want me to break you, Cohen?
- Hi.

00:24:12.640 --> 00:24:15.234
No way. Look who's back.

00:24:15.400 --> 00:24:19.188
- You're a little far from 8 Mile.
- Luke, don't.

00:24:19.360 --> 00:24:22.318
What are you, like, spokesperson
for Geeks of America or something?

00:24:22.960 --> 00:24:25.428
You know what I like about rich kids?

00:24:26.640 --> 00:24:27.629
Nothing.

00:24:28.560 --> 00:24:30.755
- That was awesome!
- Come here, you punk!

00:24:30.920 --> 00:24:32.797
Come on, man! Come here!

00:24:34.760 --> 00:24:38.309
Cohen, you're dead meat, man!
You're dead meat!

00:24:38.480 --> 00:24:39.879
Go!

00:24:41.040 --> 00:24:43.508
Come on, chump! You're dead!

00:24:51.480 --> 00:24:53.436
"You know what I like about rich kids?

00:24:54.320 --> 00:24:55.594
Nothing. " Hey, Ryan...

00:24:55.760 --> 00:24:59.196
...you wouldn't consider me rich, would
you? I'd be more upper-middle class.

00:25:02.400 --> 00:25:03.913
What's up, fool?

00:25:04.680 --> 00:25:06.716
- You know, you didn't have to hit him.
- Sorry.

00:25:06.880 --> 00:25:09.189
You know, the cashier called the cops.

00:25:12.880 --> 00:25:15.792
Look, I don't know why
Luke does that.

00:25:15.960 --> 00:25:18.235
- Did that. He's just...
- An ass?

00:25:18.720 --> 00:25:20.551
Protective.

00:25:28.080 --> 00:25:29.991
God, it's my mom.

00:25:33.360 --> 00:25:35.794
And your dad.

00:25:38.640 --> 00:25:40.437
It's been a while.

00:25:40.600 --> 00:25:44.479
I have to figure out
what kind of shape this place is in.

00:25:50.760 --> 00:25:54.514
That's what those contractors
have been doing.

00:25:56.240 --> 00:25:58.674
This place is fantastic.

00:25:58.840 --> 00:26:00.990
- You don't think it's too much?
- Are you kidding?

00:26:01.160 --> 00:26:03.469
You're talking to a guy
whose wife just imported...

00:26:03.640 --> 00:26:06.950
...ceramic shower-curtain rings
from Morocco.

00:26:10.240 --> 00:26:14.074
This is gorgeous,
with the high ceilings and the molding.

00:26:14.240 --> 00:26:16.390
It reminds me of...

00:26:16.560 --> 00:26:18.516
- Your parents' house.
- On Elm Grove.

00:26:18.680 --> 00:26:23.595
With the vaulted ceilings and those
great beams. Remember that?

00:26:23.760 --> 00:26:25.796
Yeah. I loved that old house.

00:26:25.960 --> 00:26:29.714
Yeah, I loved that place too.
I had my first kiss there.

00:26:29.880 --> 00:26:31.518
Me too.

00:26:33.000 --> 00:26:35.560
So, what's going on, Jimmy?

00:26:39.600 --> 00:26:42.876
I had a really bad year
with the market and...

00:26:43.040 --> 00:26:46.919
Well, it was disastrous. It's gonna
be a struggle just to remain solvent...

00:26:47.080 --> 00:26:49.196
How much do you need?

00:26:51.600 --> 00:26:55.229
It's... It's a lot of money.
It's too much.

00:26:55.400 --> 00:26:57.311
Jimmy.

00:26:58.640 --> 00:27:02.315
- It's $100,000.
- I'll call the bank.

00:27:02.920 --> 00:27:04.512
- No, I can't.
- I can.

00:27:05.520 --> 00:27:07.590
I'll pay you back.

00:27:10.640 --> 00:27:12.790
But it's gonna take me
a couple of months.

00:27:12.960 --> 00:27:14.712
I know where you live.

00:27:18.480 --> 00:27:20.630
This place is gonna be perfect.

00:27:21.120 --> 00:27:25.272
I hope so. The new contractors come
tomorrow. Better get the job finished.

00:27:25.440 --> 00:27:28.876
New contractors.
Sounds like a nightmare.

00:27:29.040 --> 00:27:30.996
Pretty much.

00:27:32.440 --> 00:27:34.271
Are you okay?

00:27:41.280 --> 00:27:43.999
So the contractors start tomorrow.

00:27:44.360 --> 00:27:46.669
Guess that means I'm gone.

00:27:48.560 --> 00:27:52.633
One bus ticket to Austin,
8 a.m. Tomorrow.

00:27:54.040 --> 00:27:56.190
"Would you like to purchase?"

00:28:02.240 --> 00:28:05.550
- Hey.
- Hey. We're not knocking anymore?

00:28:05.720 --> 00:28:07.438
I'm sorry. What are you doing?

00:28:07.600 --> 00:28:09.192
Just busy.

00:28:09.800 --> 00:28:13.156
- You're always busy.
- It's the price of fame. I gotta go, Dad.

00:28:13.320 --> 00:28:15.197
They found Ryan.

00:28:16.800 --> 00:28:20.031
Or spotted someone with his description.
There was a fight by the pier.

00:28:20.600 --> 00:28:21.669
Really?

00:28:21.840 --> 00:28:23.876
Which means he's probably
still in the area.

00:28:24.040 --> 00:28:27.476
We should find him before the authorities
do. Before he gets in more trouble.

00:28:27.640 --> 00:28:30.359
Actually, do you need me to go?
I was going somewhere.

00:28:30.520 --> 00:28:32.636
Seth, he's your friend.

00:28:34.240 --> 00:28:35.798
Yeah, okay.

00:28:43.320 --> 00:28:45.311
- Hey.
- Hey.

00:28:45.480 --> 00:28:47.994
So, what's up?
You've been all weird-acting lately.

00:28:48.160 --> 00:28:49.798
Yeah?

00:28:49.960 --> 00:28:52.030
I don't know, I guess...

00:28:52.200 --> 00:28:55.988
Do you ever wonder what your life
looks like through someone else's eyes?

00:28:56.160 --> 00:28:59.197
This is what I'm talking about.
What is up with you?

00:28:59.360 --> 00:29:01.351
Nothing. It's just...

00:29:01.520 --> 00:29:03.988
- Fresh margs!
- This is some weak margarita.

00:29:04.160 --> 00:29:06.310
Whatever. You're the lightweight.

00:29:07.040 --> 00:29:10.112
- Say it over here.
- I hope your parents never come home.

00:29:10.280 --> 00:29:13.272
Let's find that punk's trailer park
and burn it to the ground.

00:29:13.440 --> 00:29:14.429
Who that?

00:29:14.600 --> 00:29:16.397
That freak from Chino
was up in Luke's grill.

00:29:16.560 --> 00:29:19.677
Maybe he's on OxyContin.
OxyContin is gnarly.

00:29:19.840 --> 00:29:21.432
I heard he's a total psycho.

00:29:21.600 --> 00:29:24.637
He's a little bitch. If I see him again,
I'm gonna beat his ass.

00:29:24.800 --> 00:29:27.712
- Run him out of Newport for sure.
- I gotta go.

00:29:32.160 --> 00:29:35.311
- Hey, wait up. Where you going?
- I can't be here right now.

00:29:36.400 --> 00:29:38.152
- What's the matter?
- You don't know him.

00:29:38.320 --> 00:29:39.958
You don't know anything about him.

00:29:46.400 --> 00:29:48.630
- He could be anywhere.
- Dad, I'm sure Ryan's fine.

00:29:48.800 --> 00:29:51.234
We should try again when it's light out.

00:29:51.400 --> 00:29:55.029
- It could be too late by then.
- Maybe he's better off on his own.

00:29:55.520 --> 00:29:57.158
What does that mean?

00:29:59.360 --> 00:30:01.999
Okay, if we find him, then what?

00:30:02.160 --> 00:30:06.392
Then, if he's lucky, he gets to go back
with his mom? I would run away too.

00:30:07.600 --> 00:30:12.549
Promise me that you'd never run away,
no matter how bad things may seem.

00:30:12.720 --> 00:30:15.871
- Your mother and I will always be there.
- Take it down a notch.

00:30:16.640 --> 00:30:18.517
The minute you were born I knew...

00:30:19.200 --> 00:30:22.670
...that I would never breathe easy again
without knowing you were safe.

00:30:23.480 --> 00:30:24.833
So I'm like asthma?

00:30:25.000 --> 00:30:28.788
I'm warning you, you run away,
I'm coming with you.

00:30:31.600 --> 00:30:33.670
I guess we can keep looking.

00:30:54.800 --> 00:30:57.189
This song reminds me of you.

00:30:59.520 --> 00:31:02.398
- I thought you were with Luke.
- I was.

00:31:05.160 --> 00:31:08.436
I don't know why I'm here.
I just wanted to see you.

00:31:10.520 --> 00:31:14.513
I mean, you're leaving tomorrow,
and what if I never...?

00:31:14.680 --> 00:31:16.318
We never...?

00:31:20.800 --> 00:31:22.916
Maybe I could spend the night...

00:31:23.080 --> 00:31:24.991
...just hang out.

00:31:30.760 --> 00:31:32.796
You can't stay.

00:31:33.600 --> 00:31:37.036
If you stay, if we spend the night...

00:31:37.200 --> 00:31:39.430
- I don't know that I could leave.
- Then don't.

00:31:39.600 --> 00:31:44.355
You'll go back to school in the fall,
and I'll just what? Hang around here?

00:31:44.880 --> 00:31:47.110
Hiding like some ghost?

00:31:47.360 --> 00:31:49.669
The cops find me
and I have to disappear again?

00:31:56.120 --> 00:31:58.076
We're from different worlds.

00:31:59.680 --> 00:32:01.033
That's not true.

00:32:02.080 --> 00:32:03.991
I'm not like you.

00:32:06.720 --> 00:32:08.358
Go.

00:32:08.520 --> 00:32:10.158
Please.

00:32:10.640 --> 00:32:11.959
Go.

00:32:47.960 --> 00:32:50.076
Hey, Allen.

00:32:50.240 --> 00:32:55.234
I'm good. I know it's late,
but I need to transfer some money.

00:32:56.680 --> 00:32:58.716
Sure, I can hold on a sec.

00:33:25.760 --> 00:33:27.751
Seth, I'm up here.

00:33:28.720 --> 00:33:30.915
You get the bus ticket?

00:33:31.080 --> 00:33:32.877
Bus ticket?

00:33:34.760 --> 00:33:37.149
You're not going anywhere.

00:33:38.920 --> 00:33:41.354
What are you doing here, man?

00:33:41.520 --> 00:33:43.556
What are you doing with my girlfriend?

00:33:44.480 --> 00:33:46.072
Nothing.

00:33:46.240 --> 00:33:48.151
It didn't look like nothing.

00:33:49.160 --> 00:33:50.878
Tell me...

00:33:51.040 --> 00:33:54.271
...or I'll kill you.
- Then kill me and quit talking about it.

00:34:19.040 --> 00:34:22.271
The place is on fire, man.
We gotta go.

00:34:31.760 --> 00:34:33.318
Come on!

00:34:54.800 --> 00:34:56.677
Let's go, man!

00:34:56.840 --> 00:34:58.558
Run.

00:35:14.280 --> 00:35:16.191
I thought basketball season was over.

00:35:16.360 --> 00:35:19.875
This is ESPN Classic.
They play all old games.

00:35:20.040 --> 00:35:22.793
So the Lakers-Pistons. Right?

00:35:22.960 --> 00:35:27.351
1986, the finals, game seven.
You remember watching this?

00:35:27.520 --> 00:35:30.432
You were pregnant with Marissa
when this was on.

00:35:30.600 --> 00:35:32.830
I remember. I was so swollen.

00:35:33.000 --> 00:35:34.911
I hated Detroit.

00:35:35.080 --> 00:35:37.435
- Isiah, Laimbeer.
- Yeah.

00:35:37.600 --> 00:35:39.431
Dumars. Oh, my...

00:35:39.600 --> 00:35:43.513
But Worthy, James Worthy,
he saved us. He shot the lights out.

00:35:43.960 --> 00:35:45.359
So fantastic.

00:35:47.000 --> 00:35:49.355
You know that thing I was trying
to talk to you about?

00:35:49.520 --> 00:35:53.354
- Jimmy.
- No, I'm just saying that I took care of it.

00:35:54.920 --> 00:35:57.718
- I knew you would.
- You did?

00:36:00.360 --> 00:36:04.990
I can't believe I'm old enough to have
watched people play in those shorts.

00:36:07.640 --> 00:36:09.358
Hey, Marissa.

00:36:10.000 --> 00:36:11.399
Marissa?

00:36:15.400 --> 00:36:17.152
I'll go.

00:36:17.320 --> 00:36:18.912
Here you go.

00:36:24.960 --> 00:36:26.598
Hey.

00:36:27.960 --> 00:36:29.996
What's the matter?

00:36:31.440 --> 00:36:34.034
What's the matter? Come on.

00:36:34.200 --> 00:36:36.589
You can tell me.

00:36:38.320 --> 00:36:40.675
Come here. Give me a hug.
Give me a hug.

00:36:42.240 --> 00:36:43.753
What's the matter?

00:36:45.680 --> 00:36:49.309
You can tell me.
We tell each other everything.

00:36:51.480 --> 00:36:52.879
Do we?

00:37:01.800 --> 00:37:03.233
Hello?

00:37:06.120 --> 00:37:08.111
I'll meet you there.

00:37:17.360 --> 00:37:19.874
- Hi.
- Did Marissa come back?

00:37:20.040 --> 00:37:22.110
You smell like smoke.

00:37:23.400 --> 00:37:25.789
Yeah, we hot-boxed in Nordlund's car.

00:37:25.960 --> 00:37:28.520
And didn't invite me?

00:37:31.480 --> 00:37:34.074
Dude, that kid was messed up.

00:37:34.600 --> 00:37:37.353
- He was breathing.
- I hope so.

00:37:45.480 --> 00:37:48.313
I can't believe this.
This house is cursed.

00:37:49.480 --> 00:37:51.789
- You the owner?
- Yes, I am. What happened?

00:37:51.960 --> 00:37:54.713
Not sure yet. But it looks like
somebody's been living here.

00:37:54.880 --> 00:37:56.233
What?

00:37:57.320 --> 00:37:58.958
It's my fault.

00:38:31.200 --> 00:38:33.953
- You're okay.
- Disappointed?

00:38:34.880 --> 00:38:36.836
Where you going?

00:38:37.640 --> 00:38:39.517
Don't know.

00:38:39.680 --> 00:38:43.832
We both keep our mouths shut,
they may never know it was us.

00:38:53.600 --> 00:38:55.830
- What are you doing?
- You're giving me a ride.

00:38:56.000 --> 00:38:58.833
I don't know what happened.
I don't know why it burned down.

00:38:59.000 --> 00:39:01.719
What was he even doing there?
Why didn't you tell us?

00:39:01.880 --> 00:39:03.836
He didn't want to go to a foster home.

00:39:04.000 --> 00:39:06.833
He didn't want to leave,
and I didn't want him to leave either.

00:39:07.000 --> 00:39:09.958
It's like, you force me to live
amongst these pod people...

00:39:10.120 --> 00:39:13.396
...and the first cool person I meet,
you kick him out of the house.

00:39:21.080 --> 00:39:23.514
I did the best I could.

00:39:23.680 --> 00:39:25.511
So did I.

00:39:31.560 --> 00:39:34.757
Come on. The police want to
ask us some more questions.

00:39:34.920 --> 00:39:37.150
<i>Dispatch, is there a description...?</i>

00:39:38.000 --> 00:39:39.558
Thank you.

00:39:44.320 --> 00:39:46.231
Just follow my lead.

00:39:51.400 --> 00:39:55.712
You and I need to talk.
And this time I want the truth.

00:40:25.040 --> 00:40:28.589
- I'm sorry.
- Ryan Atwood?

00:40:30.320 --> 00:40:32.515
We got some questions for you.

00:40:39.520 --> 00:40:43.035
- It was an accident.
- Yeah, you were there?

00:40:48.840 --> 00:40:50.034
Yeah.

00:40:50.200 --> 00:40:52.668
Then we got some questions
for you too.

00:40:56.040 --> 00:40:58.759
Officer, I'm Mr. Atwood's attorney.

00:40:58.920 --> 00:41:01.992
Please don't ask him any questions
unless I'm present.

00:41:02.960 --> 00:41:05.952
Ryan, keep your mouth shut.

00:41:07.080 --> 00:41:08.798
You too.

00:00:0.500 --> 00:00:2.00
